    <p>
        The Mystical Kingdom Of Bhutan Is Arguably The Most Inaccessible And Culturally Rich Of All The Himalayan Kingdoms.
        It Is The Perfect Venue For Cycle Touring In The Himalaya, It's Compact And Has Mostly Sealed Roads Which Cross Passes In Excess Of 3000m, From Paro In The West To Bumthang In Central Bhutan.
    </p>
    <p>
        We Take In All The Highlights Including A Crossing Of The Dochu La, A Visit To Famous Punakha Dzong, Tongsa And The Gangtey Valley. There Are Plenty Of Long Mountain Climbs And Exhilarating Descents On This Tour, And So A Good Level Of Cycling Fitness Is Required. We Also Supply A Support Vehicle In Case There Are Stages Where A Little Rest And Relaxation Are Required! This Is A Unique And Rewarding Way To Experience The Himalaya At Handle Bar Level.
    </p>
